    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM MGM SPRING BRAKE - OPERATION - SERVICE BRAKE APPLICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SERVICE BRAKE APPLICATION</title>
        <para>When the service brakes are applied, air is forced into the service brake chamber (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0402003">Figure 3</hotlnk>), forcing the pushrod and piston assembly outward, extending the
            pushrod assembly.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0402003" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/G0402003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 3. Service Brake Applied</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SPRING BRAKE CHAMBER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SERVICE BRAKE CHAMBER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>When the brake (foot) valve is released, air in the service brake system is exhausted and the service
            brake chamber pushrod assembly and diaphragm are permitted to return to the normal released position (
            <hotlnk document="s04020x_1.xml" xrefid="f0402002">Figure 2</hotlnk>). The service brake spring assists in
            this function by forcing the pushrod and plate assembly into the normal released position.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
